  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Mongolia: Mitigating the Impact of COVID-19 by Increasing Children&apos;s Access to Justice</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The project aims to increase protection and access to justice for children, especially child victims of violence and those at risk in the context of COVID-19</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1) To strengthen the capacity of Legal Committees on Child Rights (LCCRs) to increase child access to justice in the context of COVID-19. 2) To increase accreditation of civil society organizations (CSOs) to provide services for children. 3) To increase awareness of the child protection and child rights framework by children, families, and communities.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="3">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Direct beneficiaries: Authority for Family, Children and Youth Development (AFCYD), National Police Agency (NPA) Child Protection Division of the Crime Prevention Unit (CPU), CSOs,
particularly those in Western and Eastern regions of

Mongolia.
Indirect beneficiaries: Vulnerable populations especially children, families and communities.</narrative>
  </description>
